Blue Bayou

Restaurant Info

 
Meals Served
 
Lunch 11:30-3:45 • Dinner 4:00-10:00

Price Range

Location
 
New Orleans Square, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
One of the favorite restaurants in Disneyland Park is the Blue Bayou. Since opening in 1967, it has become a family tradition for many Guests to dine on the delicious Cajun- and Creole-style food in a truly unique setting. Inside the Pirates of the Caribbean attraction, Guests at the Blue Bayou sit "outdoors" in perpetual twilight, surrounded by winking fireflies and the soothing sounds of the bayou's crickets and frogs, while boats filled with Guests heading into pirate-filled Caribbean waters drift past.
 
Menu
 
Lunch and dinner menus feature Louisiana classics like Tesora Island chicken, jambalaya and the famous Monte Cristo sandwich. After your meal, relax in the tranquil setting and savor a specialty dessert like fresh-baked pecan pie or crème brûlée.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Carnation Café and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Cafe Orleans

Restaurant Info

 
Meals Served
 
Lunch • Dinner

Price Range

Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Location
 
New Orleans Square, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Celebrate the spirit of Mardi Gras every day of the year at Café Orleans. On a charming shady corner in New Orleans Square, this table-service restaurant serves Creole-inspired cuisine. The authentic food and atmosphere just might make you think you've taken a trip to the French Quarter.

When you meander down the narrow streets of New Orleans Square, you are transported into a genteel world of fragrant flowers and leisurely afternoons. Sit down and relax in the gracious dining room or on the shady patio as you watch the boats on Rivers of America glide by. Close to two of the most popular attractions in Disneyland Park, Pirates of the Caribbean and the Haunted Mansion, it's also a great place to dine before Fanstasmic! during the summer.
 
Menu
 
Lunch and dinner menus feature Louisiana classics like Tesora Island chicken, jambalaya and the famous Monte Cristo sandwich. After your meal, relax in the tranquil setting and savor a specialty dessert like fresh-baked pecan pie or crème brûlée.

The specialty of the house is, without a doubt, the Monte Cristo sandwich. Adapted from the French classic sandwich, croque-monsieur, the Monte Cristo sandwich appeared in California restaurants in the 1950s. Featured at Disneyland Park eateries since 1966, it has since become a coffee shop standard nationwide.

 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Carnation Café and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Carnation Cafe

Restaurant Info

Location
 
Main Street, U.S.A., Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Stroll on in, take a break and watch the world pass down Main Street, U.S.A. at the charming Carnation Café. This cozy spot is the perfect perch for people watching and enjoying old-fashioned American diner fare under an awning of candy-cane striped umbrellas.
 
Menu
 
Beloved homey classics are the order of the day at Carnation Café. Breakfast options include Mickey-shaped waffles, apple pancakes, croissant benedict and café cinnamon roll french toast. Lunch and dinner selections feature the café steak melt, seasonal pot pie, loaded baked potato soup, croissant chicken club and chef's salad.

For dessert, enjoy delightful classics such as the Matterhorn Sundae, chocolate cake, banana splits and freshly baked apple pie á la mode.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Carnation Café and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Round-Up BBQ

Restaurant Info

 
Meals Served
 
Lunch • Dinner

Service Type
 
Unique and Themed • Casual Dining
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Location
 
Frontierland, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Chow down on cowboy-style grub in this rustic ranch setting, complete with toe-tappin' country music and an all-you-care-to-eat barbecue feast.

Follow your host down a horseshoe-studded path to a shaded table. Rest your weary bones while your table server dishes up heaping piles of food and musicians fiddle and sing.

Musical guests will keep your spirits high and your hands clapping. The musical review is the perfect way to unwind before hitting the trail to your next adventure.

 
Menu
 
At this barbecue blowout, you can have it all!

A family-style all-you-care-to-enjoy lunch includes barbeque chicken and ribs, cole slaw, ranch beans and cornbread.

At dinner, your server will bring you endless helpings of barbeque chicken and ribs, smoked sausages, cole slaw, Ranch beans, corn wheels and cornbread.

Vegetarians can request a barbecue skewer with potatoes, squash, bell peppers, mushrooms and tofu.

Dessert is available for an additional cost. You can order up an extravaganza of ranch hand sundaes and old fashioned ice cream floats, seasonal cobblers, fresh strawberry shortcake or a family-style cookie bake topped with vanilla bean ice cream and hot fudge.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Carnation Café and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Location
 
Main Street, U.S.A., Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Begin your morning at the Plaza Inn for "Minnie & Friends - Breakfast in the Park" Character Dining. It's a great way to get charged up for the day with visits from Minnie Mouse and other beloved Disney Characters.

The fixed-price buffet offers all your morning favorites including fresh-baked pastries, waffles and made-to-order omelets. Help yourself to all you care to eat while collecting autographs and taking great souvenir photos.

 
Menu
 
The Plaza Inn's lunch and dinner specialties range from broasted chicken and pot roast to pasta and salads with convenient cafeteria-style service. Children's menu selections include kid-size chicken and pasta dishes.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Carnation Café and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Location
 
New Orleans Square, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Sit a spell under hanging ferns, wrought-iron balconies and shady awnings, and savor Southern classics like jambalaya and Cajun Chicken Salad at this cafeteria-style eatery. Watch the Mark Twain Riverboat paddle down the Rivers of America, tap your toes to a Dixieland jazz band and enjoy a peaceful break in true New Orleans style.

Celebrate the spirit of New Orleans and get into the swing with some good old Dixieland jazz. The Royale Street Bachelors, a 3-piece band, perform their fun and funky tunes on the centrally located stage in the middle of the patio throughout the day.

 
Menu
 
This delightful dining experience features favorites from the American South, including Plantation Citrus Chicken, Roast Beef Royale, Salmon Creole and jambalaya. A children's menu features beloved classics like citrus chicken breast and macaroni and cheese.

Golden Horseshoe

Location
 
Frontierland, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Have a rootin', tootin', hip-hollerin' good time at the Golden Horseshoe, where the quick-service frontier-style grub will knock yer boots right off. Belly up to the bar, sit in a private box or take a seat down on the main floor and catch Billy Hill & The Hillbillies performing a must-see mix of bluegrass music and wacky comedy.

Western flair is everywhere with steer horn wall mounts, polished brass banisters and electrified period chandeliers at this 1850's-style saloon restaurant. Disney legend Harper Goff designed the interior using the saloon set he had drawn up for the 1953 Doris Day film Calamity.

 
Fun Fact
 

The Golden Horseshoe Saloon is one of the original buildings dating back to the park's opening in 1955. Walt Disney kept a private box (now public) upstairs to the left of the stage so he could watch the show. The original show, Golden Horseshoe Revue, had over 50,000 performances and was, according to the Guinness Book of World Records, "the world's longest-running live stage show."

 
Menu
 
The chuck wagon is chock full of vittles you'll love, including chicken breast tenders, fish and chips, and chili cheese fries. Buckaroos can also dig into a bonanza of desserts including the Mile High chocolate cake, mint chocolate sundae, strawberry sundae, the Golden Horseshoe Ice Cream Float and hot fudge sundae.

Ambience
 
Stroll over a wooden bridge through a forest of pine trees to a rustic retreat nestled in the shadow of Splash Mountain. This wilderness-lodge-style restaurant is a serene spot to enjoy a quick-service meal by the scenic banks of the Rivers of America.

Wave at the Mark Twain Riverboat, the Sailing Ship Columbia and Davy Crockett's Explorer Canoes as they cruise by. Look for ducks on the shores of the Rivers of America, squirrels up in the trees and other woodland creatures scouting for a stray french fry!

Kid's Meals include chicken breast tenders or hamburger and a Kid's POWER Pack with yogurt, cheese sticks, Goldfish crackers and apple slices. Location
 
Main Street, U.S.A., Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Take a break at the Victorian-theme Plaza Inn and enjoy hearty classic American fare for breakfast, lunch and dinner at one of the original Disneyland Park landmarks
 
Menu
 
The Plaza Inn's lunch and dinner specialties range from broasted chicken and pot roast to pasta and salads with convenient cafeteria-style service. Children's menu selections include kid-size chicken and pasta dishes.
 
Atmosphere
 
The ornate Victorian décor offers a grand setting for any meal. When the weather is good, you may want to dine outside on the Plaza Inn patio, which is a great spot for people watching or for viewing parades on Main Street, U.S.A.
 
History
 
The Plaza Inn, originally called the Red Wagon Inn, has been feeding hungry Guests since opening day in 1955, and was one of Walt Disney's favorite dining spots. The restaurant is decorated with authentic 19th-century furnishings, including the jewel-like Victorian stained glass and ornate woodwork salvaged from a grand old home in Los Angeles.

Location
 
Frontierland, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Bring all your amigos and indulge in classic Mexican cuisine on a beautiful bougainvillea-shaded hacienda patio. Exotic painted tiles, flowing fountains and stunning Mexican glass lanterns adorn the peaceful oasis. Sit back relax at this quick-service, fiesta-style restaurant.
.
Menu
 
Entrees include citrus fire-grilled chicken, 4 cheese enchiladas, soft tacos, burritos and even a tostada salad. Don't say "adios" without trying the Tres Leche cake, flan or chocolate praline cake.
.
History
 
"Rancho del Zocalo" translates to mean "Ranch of the Square" in English. The word "zocalo" has an interesting history at Disneyland Park. The open area at the entrance to Frontierland used to be called "El Zocalo" or "town square."
.

Location
 
Tomorrowland, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Launch into a dining adventure at this quick-service futuristic Italian eatery — and don't worry, the future still has pizza! Refuel your whole crew and eat outside near the famed Moonliner rocket beneath the shadow of Space Mountain. Or sit inside the Port among the old visionary posters from Disneyland Park history.
.
Menu
 
This spaceport is fully equipped with earthling food, including space-age favorites like Mars-inara with Meteoric Meatballs, Countdown Chicken Fusilli and Mega slices of pepperoni, cheese or vegetarian pizza.
.
History
 
Redd Rockett's Pizza Port is located in the former location of the Mission to Mars attraction, which offered daily flights to the red planet from 1975 to 1992. The vintage posters on the back wall are a must-see for any Disney history buff.

Frontierland, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
Stroll through an illustrious Ante-bellum entrance and discover a sweet spot for Southern hospitality and down-home comfort food. Dine at this counter-service restaurant under elegant wrought-iron chandeliers or sit a spell on the shade-dappled terrace and watch the Mark Twain Steamboat paddle down the Rivers of America.
.
Menu
 
For breakfast, indulge in the ever-popular Mickey Mouse Pancakes or heaping helpings of scrambled eggs and bacon. During lunch or dinner, don't miss the Signature Sandwiches served on soft baguettes, featuring turkey breast, barbecued pork or savory vegetables. All sandwiches are accompanied by southern baked beans and your choice of a side.
.
History
 
Offering one of the most picturesque views of the Rivers of the America, The River Belle Terrace building is one of the original Disneyland Park eateries, dating back to the park's opening in 1955. Walt Disney had breakfast here on innumerable Sunday mornings.

Location
 
Fantasyland, Disneyland
 
Ambience
 
During your trek through Fantasyland, discover this gable-roofed storybook house with a quick-service restaurant — it's the perfect spot to relax and enjoy some tasty American classics. Village Haus is inspired by Gepetto's home from the animated 1940 masterpiece Pinocchio.
 
Menu
 
Every real boy and girl will enjoy dining options that include premium cheeseburgers, chicken sausage sandwiches, veggie burgers, BLT flat bread pizzas, pepperoni and cheese pizzas, apple cheddar salads and our new signature Pastrami Cheeseburger. For a delicious fairytale ending, try our black forest cupcake or apple strudel.
 
Inspiration
 
The design of Village Haus mirrors the classic opening sequence from Pinocchio. Search for hidden treasures in nooks and crannies like real puppets, cuckoo-clocks, and wood carved knick-knacks. The atmosphere is so convincing that you almost believe that somewhere around here, Gepetto must be hard at work! As you enjoy your meal, follow the murals that tell the tale of the puppet who longed to be a real boy.

Ariel's Grotto

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Breakfast • Lunch • Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
American • Healthy Selections • Vegetarian
 
Price Range
 
More Than $36 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Character Dining • Unique and Themed • Casual Dining
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Location
 
Paradise Pier, California Adventure
 
Ambience
 
Join Ariel and her friends at Ariel's Grotto for an enchanting Character Dining experience filled with music, laughter, delicious food and the opportunity to meet Disney Princesses during "Ariel's Disney Princess Celebration."
 
The Characters
 
Children of all ages are thrilled to meet their favorite Disney Princesses up close! Bring your camera and capture the magic, framed by a beautiful mural of an underwater scene, while you collect autographs, greet Disney Princesses — including Snow White, Cinderella and Sleeping Beauty and enjoy a most unforgettable time.

Character Dining at Ariel's Grotto is available for breakfast and lunch.
 
Atmosphere
 
Descend the spiral staircase to enter Ariel's Grotto, and attend a royal undersea banquet with Ariel and her friends. From the themed décor to the view of Paradise Bay through the windows, you're surrounded by imagery from under the sea.

Choose to be seated indoors or enjoy a closer view of the water and dine on the outdoor patio; Characters visit Guests at all table locations.

 
Menu
 
Select your entrée from the fixed-price menu where choices range from pasta and slow-roasted tri-tip to seafood soup; kids enjoy chicken on sugar cane skewers, spaghetti and more. Meals at Ariel's Grotto include family-style salads and desserts
 
Cove Bar
 
Upstairs from Ariel's Grotto, you'll find the open-air Cove Bar. Find a seat under the gazebo roof or on the open patio where you can relax and enjoy fresh air and a scenic view of Paradise Bay while sampling delicious appetizers like lobster nachos. Guests 21 and older can sip signature cocktails, beer or wine.
 
World of Color
 
Take "dinner and a show" to a whole new level! Secure a great vantage point for World of Color with a full-service prix fixe dinner at Ariel's Grotto that includes tickets to a Preferred Viewing section at Paradise Park. Learn more about World of Color dining packages, including times, prices and how to book your meal.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are recommended for Ariel's Grotto and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Wine Country Trattoria

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Lunch • Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
Italian • Healthy Selections • Vegetarian
 
Price Range
 
$15 to $35.99 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Unique and Themed
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Location
 
Golden State, California Adventure
 
Ambience
 
Feel like you're in the heart of Napa Valley at Wine Country Trattoria, where a passion for wine and fresh seasonal ingredients creates the ideal setting for a leisurely afternoon or romantic dinner.

The dappled plaster walls, tile flooring and timber accents are reminiscent of a Tuscan villa. Dine indoors or al fresco on a broad umbrella-dotted terrace that features a hand-carved limestone fountain and beds of fragrant flowers and herbs. Or simply relax with a glass of wine on the Medocino Terrace.

 
Wine List
 
With more than 25 different wines by the glass, select the perfect pairing to complement your meal. From Carneros to Venice, many of the world's top wine growing regions are represented on the extensive wine list. Not sure what to order? Wine flights are a great way to sample the restaurant's cellar.
 
Menu
 
Savor Californian and Mediterranean influences with house specialties that include fresh seafood, braised meats, pasta just the way you like it and an irresistible finalé, Tiramisù. Lunch selections include entrée salads and grilled Panini.
 
World of Color
 
Take "dinner and a show" to a whole new level! Secure a great vantage point for World of Color with a full-service prix fixe dinner at Wine Country Trattoria that includes tickets to a Preferred Viewing section at Paradise Park. Learn more about World of Color dining packages, including times, prices and how to book your meal.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are recommended and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Boardwalk Pizza & Pasta prepares hearty Italian favorites with a California twist.

Taste flatbread pizza as it's pulled piping hot from the ovens at this eatery in the food court marketplace on the Paradise Pier Boardwalk. Delicious pizza, pasta dishes and salads are prepared quickly in on-stage kitchens.

 
Try some of these inventive signature items:

Tomato sauce, pesto, spinach, Portobello mushrooms, artichokes and mozzarella

Romaine, iceberg and spinach, topped with blue cheese, dried cranberries, caramelized pecans and a basil vinaigrette
 
There are also traditional favorites like spaghetti and meatballs, 5-cheese ravioli, pepperoni pizza or a chicken Caesar salad.

Pacific Wharf Cafe

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Snacks • Breakfast • Lunch • Dinner

American • Californian • Healthy Selections • Vegetarian

Premium 15%

So-Cal Select 10%
 
Location
 
Pacific Wharf, California Adventure
 
Atmosphere
 
Drop anchor and take a break on the peaceful waterfront at the Pacific Wharf Café — a charming counter-service restaurant from Boudin Bakery, the famous artisanal bakery in San Francisco. Soak up the sunny day, watch the ducks float by or toss a penny into the sparkling blue Paradise Bay and make a wish.
 
Menu
 
Representing the culinary excellence that is the Bay Area, the Café's specialties include the Salinas turkey sandwich and the Carmel roast beef sandwich. Warm up with a host of hearty soups, including Monterey clam chowder, Bakersfield broccoli and cheese, Santa Rosa corn chowder and Vallejo vegetarian chili ¾ all served in a sourdough bread bowl made from a secret family recipe dating back to 1849.

For those wanting a lighter meal, 3 Golden State salads are also served in the famous sourdough bread bowl.

For the younger generation, the Café offers a Kid's turkey wrap and a Kid's POWER Pack — with string cheese, non-fat yogurt, sliced apples and whole-grain "fish" crackers. Both include a choice of beverage.

Don't forget to save room for nearly a baker's dozen of treats for dessert!
 
Bakery Secrets
 
Don't miss The Bakery Tour, hosted by Boudin Bakery right next to the Pacific Wharf Café. Peer through glass walls and discover the 150-year-old secrets that make this sourdough bread so delicious!
 
History
 
Boudin Bakery is San Francisco's oldest continuously running company. In 1849, Boudin was a tiny, old-world shop on San Francisco's Dupont Street. Since then, it has evolved to a world-famous bakery renowned for using the finest ingredients available.

Ambience
 

This fast and casual eatery on the Paradise Pier Boardwalk offers a savory Mediterranean menu with zesty beef, chicken and vegetarian selections.

Taste Pilot's

Restaurant Info

Location
 
Condor Flats, California Adventure
 
Ambience
 
Soar into the future of flight with the best comfort food available on base. Refuel like a fly-boy with gourmet burgers, ribs and chicken sandwiches inside this quick-service restaurant.
 
Menu
 
3 kinds of burgers are offered, but don't forget the chicken sandwiches, the pork ribs and the "Supersonic Salad." The child's menu offers chicken breast nuggets, mini burgers and the Kid's POWER Pack with string cheese, nonfat yogurt, sliced apples and whole-grain "fish" crackers.

Test pilots of all ages should leave room for a delicious "Sound Barrier Shake" topped with whipped cream. Budweiser, Bud Light and Karl Strauss Handcrafted Beer are available. Guests must be 21 years or older to consume alcoholic beverages.
 
Theme
 
This 1950's hanger-themed restaurant is an authentic quonset hut constructed of corrugated steel. Rocketing out from above the main entrance is a model of a real X-1 rocket plane, the first aircraft to exceed the speed of sound. Take some time to enjoy real pictures and schematics from NASA and the McDonnell Douglas Labs.

Catal

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Breakfast • Lunch • Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
Mediterranean • Healthy Selections • Vegetarian • Steak
 
Price Range
 
$15 to $35.99 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Full Service
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 10%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Every Day
Not during Special Events
 
Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Savor, celebrate and indulge in old-world romance at a restaurant where homespun hospitality meets gourmet cuisine. Catal Restaurant specializes in modern interpretations of classic Mediterranean favorites. Dine inside or enjoy the airy patio with a sparkling second-story view overlooking the Downtown Disney District.
 
Menu
 
Dinner selections include exquisite creations such as paella á la Valencia, housemade squid ink pasta, roasted duck breast with fresh corn polenta, rack of lamb and braised angus short ribs. Catal features inventive salads such as an organic mixed lettuce salad with cherries, Manchego cheese salad with dates, and an endive salad with bleu cheese, pears and candied pecans.

Breakfast selections include a wild mushroom omelet, chilaquiles, smoked salmon hash and brioche French toast.

The children's menu features favorites like burgers, macaroni, pot pies and chicken fingers — and the menu comes with fun-filled activities and games!
 
Uva Bar and Café
 
Enjoy a more casual dining experience downstairs from Catal, featuring both indoor and outdoor seating. With over 40 wines by the glass, a magnificent open-air circular bar, tasty tapas and daily happy hours, Uva Bar is the ideal spot to have a drink and hang out. The hip metro-station architecture — inspired by the 1920's Jazz Age — provides a unique atmosphere. The Patina Restaurant Group
 
Patina Restaurant Group
 
Catal Restaurant is brought to Downtown Disney from world-renowned Patina Restaurant Group, which has realized some of the finest restaurants in the world. Under the leadership of Chef Joachim Splichal, the group runs over 60 dining establishments at cultural landmarks across America.
 
Reservations
 

Reservations can be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

ESPN Zone

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Lunch • Dinner

Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
An eye-catching marquee featuring sports news and trivia illuminates the entrance to this temple of all things ESPN! Whether you're craving a sit-down dining experience or want to catch the game on one of over 120 HDTVs — including one that measures 16 feet — you'll walk away feeling like a winner!
 
Menu
 
Kick off with classic starters like buffalo wings, Zone queso chips, sliders, and mahi-mahi tostadas. Next, step up to the plate with savory salads and entrees that feature baby back ribs, Angus New York strip, roasted chicken, grilled salmon and a large variety of delicious burgers. Finally, score a taste touchdown with a Chocolate Chip Cookie Sundae or any of the ESPN Zone's decadent desserts.

For rookies ages 12 and under, a Kid's Menu features favorites like macaroni and cheese, chicken nuggets and mini cheeseburgers.
 
Sports Arena
 
Bring it at the ESPN Zone Sports Arena! This 10,000-square-foot, interactive sports arcade located on the second floor includes the NHL 2 Night hockey rink, ESPN Hoops Hysteria and ESPN Zone Football Challenge. With over 40 games and 80 stations to compete on, this action-packed arena will keep you scoring for hours on end!
 
Souvenirs
 
Take home a piece of the action with a trip to the ESPN Zone Studio Store, home to sports clothing, collectibles and memorabilia for every fan.
 
Reservations
 

Limited seating may be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. ESPN Zone does not take direct reservation requests as seating is first come, first served for most parties. If you're interested in booking a party with 30+ guests, please contact the Sales Team at (714) 300-ESPN or (714) 300-3776. You must be 18 or over to dial these phone numbers.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

 
Tip
 
Go to http://www.espnzone.com/mvp/ to join ESPN Zone's MVP Club to make priority seating as well as seating location requests.

House of Blues

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Brunch • Lunch • Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
American • Cajun-Creole • Steak
 
Price Range
 
$15 to $35.99 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Unique and Themed • Casual Dining • Bars and Lounges
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 20%
Deluxe 20%
So-Cal 20%
So-Cal Select 20%
 
Every Day
Before 5 p.m.
 
Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Celebrate the spirit of the American South with world-class live music and lip-smacking soul food at this plantation-style estate turned rollicking rock n' roll palace. Feast on delectable Delta-inspired dishes and enjoy the funky American folk art and live musical performances on the House of Blues® Stage.
 
Menu
 
Kick off your soul food feast with savory appetizers like pan-seared voodoo shrimp, chicken and shrimp gumbo, Mississippi sliders and spicy buffalo wings. Southern sandwich selections include BBQ pulled pork sandwich and the crispy shrimp po' boy.

Down-home entrees feature favorites like Cajun meatloaf, Creole seafood jambalaya and grilled ribeye. And the show's not over until you polish off a decadent dessert like white chocolate banana bread pudding or Florida key lime pie.

A full bar and cocktail menu is available at House of Blues Anaheim.

Host your meeting or special event at House of Blues. This venue offers group dining menus, unique party and banquet spaces, and professional meeting and event planners.

After your meal, take home some unique gifts from the House of Blues® Company Store.
 
Gospel Brunch
 
Raise your spirits every Sunday at the inspiring, electrical and delicious Gospel Brunch! Sensational gospel choirs take to the stage while you dig into an amazing breakfast buffet, featuring home-style favorites like Alaskan snow crab, oysters on the half shell, biscuits and gravy, Southern fried chicken, custom omelets, herb-crusted roast beef and french toast sticks with all the fixin's.
 
Live Music
 
House of Blues® Stage is home to the best musical talent, featuring today's hottest bands, international world music, funk and soul artists and emerging regional talent. From R&B, hip-hop and Latin to reggae, rock and the blues— everything goes at the House of Blues!
 
Southern Arts and Legends
 
House of Blues Anaheim is home to a collection of famous antique quilts of Gees Bend, Alabama. These art pieces are so treasured, they have even appeared on United States postage stamps. In tribute, the Main Stage curtain is called the "Crazy Quilt," and a metal box of real Mississippi Delta mud is buried underneath the stage.
 
Reservations
 
Reservations are recommended and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

La Brea Bakery

Restaurant Info

Brunch • Lunch • Dinner • Snacks

Every Day .
 
Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Follow the irresistible aroma of baking bread to this lovely Craftsman-style café, featuring sandwiches on fine artisan breads, fresh salads and eclectic California cuisine. Grab a bite at the quick-service counter or take a seat on the delightful patio and enjoy the table-service restaurant outdoors.
 
Menu
 
The baker is in! Don't miss the signature sandwiches, soups served in sourdough bread bowls, grilled paninis, sliders and pizza-style flatbreads. They're all delicious and they're all served on La Brea Bakery's world-famous breads!
 
History
 
The first La Brea Bakery was opened in 1989 by top chef Nancy Silverton. She won the prestigious James Beard award for "Pastry Chef of the Year" in 1990. Since then, La Brea breads have been considered by many the standard for artisanal breads throughout the country.

Silverton is also known as the creator of Campanile Restaurant, a cherished Los Angeles eatery. In 2006, she partnered with Mario Batali and Joe Bastianich to open Osteria Mozza, which has since been hailed by critics as one of the finest new restaurants in Southern California.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for La Brea Bakery Café and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Celebrate the charm, cuisine and comfort of southern Italy at this classic Neapolitan restaurant. The pizza-toting harlequin statue above the door promises both good food and good times. With 2 levels of table-service, wood-fired pizzas and an award-winning wine list, there's something delightful for the entire family!
 
Menu
 
Everything on the menu says bellissima! Favorites include calamari fritti, fresh pastas with seasonal ingredients, Caprese salad and, of course, authentic Neapolitan pizzas. With over 20 wines served by the glass, don't forget to try one of the many Californian or Italian vintages selected from the enormous 2-story wine cellar.

If you're on the go, stop by the adjacent quick-service location, Napolini, where you'll find fresh salads, pastas, panini and pizza by the slice.
 
History
 
Naples Ristorante e Pizzeria is the brainchild of the famous Patina Restaurant Group. The group, started by famed restaurateur Nick Valenti and master Chef Joachim Splichal, is known for providing world-class cuisine throughout the United States.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Naples Ristorante e Pizzeria and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Reservations are not available for the quick-service Napolini.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Atmosphere
 
Rainforest Cafe in Downtown Disney brings adventure to the lunch and dinner table with outstanding American cuisine that includes luscious salads, pasta, sandwiches, seafood, burgers and poultry dishes, as well as a variety of vegetarian selections and kid-friendly meals.

Top off your dining safari with a signature desert such as the Sparkling Volcano, a chocolate brownie tower topped with ice cream, whipped cream and caramel and chocolate sauces—it's erupting with sweet goodness!
 
A Wild Place to Shop and Eat!
 
Reservations are recommended for this popular themed restaurant where animated animals roam the rainforest as the sky claps with the boom of simulated thunder and sudden rainstorms. (Don't worry—you won't get wet!) Lush vegetation, banyan trees, waterfalls, trumpeting elephants and chest-pounding gorillas round out the rich jungle ambiance.

Jazz Kitchen Express

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Breakfast • Lunch • Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
Cajun-Creole • Steak
 
Price Range
 
$15 to $35.99 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Special & Unique Dining • Bars and Lounges
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 10%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Every Day
 
Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Pass under the striped awning of Ralph Brennan's Jazz Kitchen and you'll think you've been transported to the French Quarter. The authentic New Orleans cuisine and nightly live jazz make this a great spot to dine and relax.
 
Menu
 
Feast on traditional Big Easy favorites like muffellattas, gumbo ya-ya, jambalaya and catfish, or traditional fare like juicy steaks or fresh salads. For the perfect ending to your meal, be sure to order bananas Foster or fresh hot beignets.
 
Entertainment
 
Listen to the sounds of jazz at Flambeaux's Jazz Club — live every night. From toe-tapping Dixieland to the smoother side of jazz, the changing music menu offers something to please every jazz lover.
 
Décor
 
The Jazz Kitchen's courtyard is lined with ornate iron railings and lush plants with a bubbling fountain in the center. Inside you'll find authentic French Quarter touches, like the colorful Mardi Gras umbrellas hanging from the ceiling.
 
Sunday Brunch
 
Start your Sunday with delicious food, live music and astonishing magicians at "Nawlin's Brunch Fest." Adults choose from a special menu featuring breakfast favorites, lunch items and entrée salads. Kids have their very own buffet. Guests 21 and older can visit our own Bloody Mary Chef for a made-to-order morning cocktail. Sunday brunch is available from 10:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
 
In a Hurry?
 
Not to worry! Enjoy a taste of New Orleans to go at Jazz Kitchen Express where you can grab fresh beignets and coffee or choose from a selection of the restaurant's specialties like jambalaya, gumbo ya-ya and homemade bread pudding.

Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Ralph Brennan's Jazz Kitchen (not Jazz Kitchen Express) and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Tortilla Jo's

Every Day
 
Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Every señor and señorita will find something to enjoy in this brightly colored multi-story cantina with savory, spicy Mexican cuisine, served with south of the border hospitality. On the move? Visit the attached Taqueria at Tortilla Jo's for a casual quick bite.
 
Menu
 
The festive menu includes customizable tacos and burritos, Mayan spiced salmon and Jo's famous carnitas. And don't miss the made-to-order guacamole!
 
Tequila Bar
 
The impressive tequila bar offers over 100 selections in 3 categories — blanco, reposado and añejo. Adventurous palates can sample mezcal and rare bottles of añejo exceptionale.
 
Patina Restaurant Group
 
Tortilla Jo's is run by the famous Patina Restaurant Group, started by famed restaurateur Nick Valenti and master Chef Joachim Splichal, and known for providing world-class cuisine throughout the United States.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Tortilla Jo's and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Reservations are not available for the quick-service Taqueria at Tortilla Jo's.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Savor, celebrate and indulge in old-world romance at a restaurant where homespun hospitality meets gourmet cuisine. Catal Restaurant specializes in modern interpretations of classic Mediterranean favorites. Dine inside or enjoy the airy patio with a sparkling second-story view overlooking the Downtown Disney District.
 
Uva Bar and Café
 
Enjoy a more casual dining experience downstairs from Catal, featuring both indoor and outdoor seating. With over 40 wines by the glass, a magnificent open-air circular bar, tasty tapas and daily happy hours, Uva Bar is the ideal spot to have a drink and hang out. The hip metro-station architecture — inspired by the 1920's Jazz Age — provides a unique atmosphere. The Patina Restaurant Group
 
Patina Restaurant Group
 
Catal Restaurant is brought to Downtown Disney from world-renowned Patina Restaurant Group, which has realized some of the finest restaurants in the world. Under the leadership of Chef Joachim Splichal, the group runs over 60 dining establishments at cultural landmarks across America.

Napa Rose

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
American • Californian • Healthy Selections • Vegetarian
 
Price Range
 
More Than $36 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Signature Dining • Bars and Lounges
 
Location
 
Grand Californian Hotel & Spa
 
Napa Rose
 
This elegant award-winning restaurant offers an incomparable selection of wines and serves contemporary cuisine inspired by California's rich bounty of fine, fresh ingredients. Whether you celebrate a special occasion or take a break from a busy day at Disneyland Resort, you'll savor an exceptional dining experience.
 
Menu
 
The seasonally changing menu offers unique fresh tastes. Start off with appetizers like hand-harvested diver scallops or portobello mushroom bisque "Cappuccino." Dine on house specialties like strawberry sage barbeque duck breast or spit-roasted prime rib of pork with ranch-style black beans. The chef's 4-course prix-fixe tasting menu changes weekly.
 
Atmosphere
 
The interior of Napa Rose is rich in authentic handcrafted Arts and Crafts details. Whether you are seated at a table with a view of Disney California Adventure Park or with the few lucky Guests at the exhibition kitchen-view counter, you're surrounded by artful details like inlaid wood paneling and leaded glass windows.
 
Napa Rose Lounge
 
Inside the Napa Rose, you'll also find a cozy lounge — great for relaxing with a glass of wine and an outstanding appetizer or sipping a nightcap and indulging in one of the sensational desserts.
 
Service
 
From the moment you enter Napa Rose, the attentive staff sees to your every need. Wine novices and experts alike appreciate the service from the expert sommeliers that assist you in selecting just the right bottle from the award-winning collection of California wines.
 
Accolades
 
Since opening in 2002, Napa Rose has garnered many distinguished awards for excellence, including:
  • Number one food ranking in the Zagat Survey for Orange County restaurants in 2002, 2003 and 2004
  • Zagat's Orange County "Most Popular Restaurant" in 2008 and 2009
  • Orange County Business Journal's "Best Southern California Restaurant 2007"
  • Wine Spectator's "Best of Award of Excellence"
  • Distinguished Restaurants of North America (DiRoNA) award of excellence for the second time in 2007
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are recommended for Napa Rose and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Location
 
Grand Californian Hotel & Spa
 
Storyteller's Cafe
 
Classic children's books come to life at this inviting restaurant at Disney's Grand Californian Hotel & Spa that celebrates the age-old tradition of storytelling. Storytellers Café features a daily Character Breakfast hosted by Chip 'n Dale.
 
Character Breakfast
 
Join the lively Chip 'n Dale Critter Breakfast for an unforgettable experience filled with music and lots of interactive fun featuring some of your favorite woodland friends. You may order from the menu or select your favorites from the Farmer's Market buffet that serves up Mickey Mouse-shaped waffles, fresh fruit and made to order omelets.
 
Atmosphere
 
Around the room, discover details like the 7 hand-painted murals, each depicting classic California stories like Mark Twain's "The Jumping Frogs of Calaveras County" and Scott O'Dell's "Island of the Blue Dolphins." On chilly days, warm yourself by the roaring fire.
 
Menu
 
Serving delicious foods morning 'til night, many dishes have a California inspiration, like Sonoma Valley Braised Chicken and Lemon Prawns. The lunch menu offers a variety of salads, soups and sandwiches. For dinner, select from buffet selections or order menu specialties from fresh pastas to juicy steaks.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are recommended for "Chip 'n' Dale Critter Breakfast" and other meals and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Atmosphere
 
Join Chef Goofy and some other favorite Disney Characters at this whimsical buffet-service restaurant where everyone's a kid! Dine on a wide selection of delicious dishes and laugh it up during your meal.
 
Character Dining
 
Enjoy a fun-filled breakfast or dinner like no other! Your host, Goofy, welcomes you to the action where boisterous fun is the order of the day. Enjoy all you care to eat while snapping memorable photos with Goofy and the gang. Gawrsh!
 
Menu
 
For breakfast, enjoy favorites like made-to-order omelets and fresh baked pastries or specialties like Mickey Mouse-shaped waffles and Goofy's Peanut Butter Pizza. Dinner choices range from salads to prime rib. Be sure to save room for top-your-own soft serve yogurt!
 
Location
 
Goofy's Kitchen is located in the Disneyland Hotel and is convenient to anyone staying at or visiting the Disneyland Resort.
 
Reservations

Steakhouse 55

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Breakfast • Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
American • Healthy • Selections • Steak • Vegetarian
 
Price Range
 
More Than $36 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Signature Dining • Bars and Lounges
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Every Day
 
Location
 
Disneyland Hotel
 
Atmosphere
 
For a delicious breakfast or elegant dinner, Steakhouse 55 at the Disneyland Hotel offers a fresh update on the classic steakhouse concept with an intimate ambiance and a renowned wine cellar.
 
Menu
 
Begin your day of magic with a relaxing breakfast of steak and eggs, eggs benedict, huevos rancheros or one of the healthful menu choices. Kids can dig into Mickey-shaped pancakes or a just-right sized serving of scrambled eggs.

At dinner, start your meal with the famous Seven Onion Soup or one of the fresh salad selections. Tender cuts of certified Angus beef seasoned with the restaurant's signature rub are definitely the focus of the menu, but you can also order one of the fresh seafood choices or delectable lamb, pork or chicken. Guests 21 and older can select a bottle of wine from the extensive wine list or have our sommeliers expertly pair wines with their meal. Don't forget to complete your meal with one of our signature desserts.

Prix-fixe and children's menus are available. The private Oak Room may be reserved for parties of up to 24 Guests.
 
Atmosphere
 
When you enter Steakhouse 55, you may think you've stepped into an old-time Hollywood club. From the oversize photos of movie and music luminaries to the cozy banquettes and attentive service, the extraordinary setting will make any meal memorable.
 
The Lounge at Steakhouse 55
 
Stop in to the Lounge at Steakhouse 55 for a quiet place to enjoy a light snack and a glass of wine or other libation. Select from the restaurant's excellent wine list or sample one of the savory appetizers.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are recommended for Steakhouse 55 and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Tangaroa Terrace

Restaurant Info

Meals Served
 
Breakfast • Lunch • Dinner • Snacks
 
Cuisine Type
 
American • Healthy Selections
 
Price Range
 
Less Than $14.99 Per Person
 
Service Type
 
Quick Service • Casual Dining
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Every Day
 
Location
 
Disneyland Hotel
 
Atmosphere
 
Tangaroa Terrace - Casual Island Dining is a tropical retreat complete with lit torches and music from the South Seas. Named for the most magical of gods from the Enchanted Tiki Room, it is located between the Monorail Slide and D-Ticket pools.

Whether you are ready to Grab-n-Go or would prefer to eat on island time, there are signature items for every meal of the day.
 
Breakfast Signature Items
 
Start the day with French toast with bacon and warm banana-caramel sauce or grilled cinnamon-spiced oatmeal cakes and much more.
 
Lunch Signature Items
 
Dive in to a 1/3 pound Hawaiian cheeseburger with teriyaki sauce, bacon and grilled pineapple served on a multi-grain roll or try lighter fare like Asian chicken salad with diced chicken breast with red and gold peppers tossed in sesame vinaigrette.
 
Dinner Signature Items
 
Relax each evening as the sun goes down with a different Island Plate Dinner. Specialty entrees include miso-crusted salmon, tamarind-glazed island pork shanks or panko-crusted chicken prepared "Katsu"-style. All entrees are served with jasmine rice, panko-crusted Chinese long beans, and green papaya slaw.
 
Grab-N-Go
 
Quick eats to take on the go include a variety of different options, from fresh yogurt parfait with seasonal berries and granola to fresh veggies to sweet potato cake with guava cream cheese icing. No matter where you're headed at Disneyland Resort, there is something for everyone to bring along.

Atmosphere
 
Welcome, Brave Adventurers!

Dock your tramp steamer at the cement shores of the Disneyland Hotel pool area and enter this mystical, interactive experience.

Bold and unforgettable cruise-ine awaits at this tiki bar inspired by the world-famous Jungle Cruise. Trader Sam's - named for the "head" salesman of the Amazon — features some of the exotic wares he has collected over the years. But beware...he's always looking for a good trade.
 
A Tropical Tiki Menu
 
Guests can voyage beyond mere bar food with panko-crusted Chinese long beans with sriracha mayonnaise, sweet 'n spicy Asian wings and Ahi Poke — a wasabi-yuzu-marinated ahi tuna served with avocado, green onion and crispy wontons.

Location
 
Paradise Pier Hotel
 
Disney's PCH Grill
 
The famed Pacific Coast Highway along California's golden coast is the inspiration behind Disney's PCH Grill at Disney's Paradise Pier Hotel. With fresh, California-inspired cuisine served in a beach-themed atmosphere, this colorful restaurant offers a sun-filled family dining experience.
 
Menu
 
There's something for everyone! Enjoy popular American favorites with a fresh California twist. For dinner, choose from burgers, steaks, salads and flatbreads from the wood-burning oven or start your morning with the Surf's Up! Breakfast with Mickey & Friends buffet at Disney's PCH Grill.
 
Surf's Up! Breakfast with Mickey & Friends
 
The Surf's Up! Breakfast with Mickey & Friends is a lively Character Dining experience that features a bountiful breakfast buffet filled with morning delights. Snap photos, practice hula hooping and hang ten with some of your favorite Disney Characters! Feast on family favorites from the omelet station and let your kids create their own breakfasts at the fun kid's buffet. Scrumptious breakfast specialties include flatbreads from the wood-burning oven, grilled breast of chicken with roasted garlic sauce and signature chilaquiles with shredded beef, salsa verde and queso fresco.

Character Dining at Disney's PCH Grill is available for breakfast.
 
Atmosphere
 
Life's a beach at Disney's PCH Grill! With blue skies overhead, surfboard decorations, oversized kites floating from the ceiling and colorful décor, turn your casual dining experience into the flavorful beach day.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are recommended for Disney's PCH Grill and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Location
 
Downtown Disney District
 
Atmosphere
 
Follow the irresistible aroma of baking bread to this lovely Craftsman-style café, featuring sandwiches on fine artisan breads, fresh salads and eclectic California cuisine. Grab a bite at the quick-service counter or take a seat on the delightful patio and enjoy the table-service restaurant outdoors.
 
Menu
 
The baker is in! Don't miss the signature sandwiches, soups served in sourdough bread bowls, grilled paninis, sliders and pizza-style flatbreads. They're all delicious and they're all served on La Brea Bakery's world-famous breads!
 
History
 
The first La Brea Bakery was opened in 1989 by top chef Nancy Silverton. She won the prestigious James Beard award for "Pastry Chef of the Year" in 1990. Since then, La Brea breads have been considered by many the standard for artisanal breads throughout the country.

Silverton is also known as the creator of Campanile Restaurant, a cherished Los Angeles eatery. In 2006, she partnered with Mario Batali and Joe Bastianich to open Osteria Mozza, which has since been hailed by critics as one of the finest new restaurants in Southern California.

Carthay Circle

Restaurant Info

 
Meals Served
 
Lunch • Dinner
 
Cuisine Type
 
American • Vegetarian • Health Selections
 
Price Range
 
More Than $36 Per Person
 
Meals Served
 
Signature Dining
 
Annual Pass Discount
 
Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Location
 
Buena Vista Street, California Adventure
 
Ambience
 

Carthay Circle Restaurant is located on the second floor of the iconic reproduction of the Cathay Circle Theatre. The original Cathay Circle Theatre played a very significant role in the life of Walt Disney; it was the location where his first feature-length film, Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs, premiered in 1937. The décor of Carthay Circle Restaurant reflects the romance and refinement of Hollywood's Golden Age, including references to the accomplishments of Walt Disney and his original animators.

Seating is available in the main dining room, 2 open-air terraces and the Premiere Room, a private dining room that can accommodate parties of up to 12 people.
 
Menu
 

For lunch, Carthay Circle Restaurant offers a variety of delectable dishes, including fire cracker duck wings, grilled Angus flank steak Cobb salad and sautéed northern halibut. The dinner menu includes halibut ceviche, strawberry-lemon roasted organic chicken salad, grilled Jamaican jerked king fish and Colorado rack of lamb. Kids can enjoy chicken schnitzel, mini tacos, green apple caramel parfait and sloppy joes with a twist.

The dessert highlights are toasted lemon pound cake, fried banana split Monte Cristo sundae and the decadent white-chocolate mousse named Peaches in All of Their Glory.
 
World of Color Dining Packages
 

When you purchase an entrée and either an appetizer or a dessert, you are eligible to receive a ticket granting you access to a Reserved Center Stage Viewing Area for the World of Color nighttime water spectacular.
Guests dining before 7:00 p.m. receive access to the first World of Color show of the night. Guests dining between 7:00 p.m. and 9:00 p.m. receive access to the second World of Color show of the night.
 
Lounge
 

The first floor of the Cathay Circle Theatre features the Carthay Circle Lounge, which serves appetizers, tapas and desserts, plus craft beer, California wines, seltzer sodas and specialty cocktails. Each cocktail is given exceptional attention to detail — including unique glassware and drink-specific ice.
 
Reservations
 
Dining reservations are available for Carnation Café and can be made in person for this location on a limited basis. Reservations can also be arranged in advance by calling Disney Dining at (714) 781-DINE or (714) 781-3463. Guests under age 18 must have parent or guardian permission to call.

Tip: To reach a Disney Dining represenative faster press 1 then 4 on your phone's keypad.

Buena Vista Street, California Adventure
 
Ambience
 

Enjoy a pleasant breakfast, lunch or dinner at this charming sidewalk café that serves sandwiches, soups, pastries and some of your favorite Starbucks beverages.
 
Menu
 

Fiddler, Fifer & Practical Café is the perfect place to start your day with a cup of coffee and a pastry or breakfast sandwich. For lunch and dinner, the café serves up tasty soups and sandwiches.

The café's specialties include:

  • Cinnamon rolls
  • Roast beef and cheddar sandwiches
  • Turkey Ruebens
  • Paneer and roasted vegetable sandwiches
  • Salami with olive tapenade sandwiches

Each day 2 house-made soups are available from a rotating selection that includes:

  • Vegetarian cream spinach
  • Chicken tortilla
  • Portobello barley
  • Hearty meaty stew
  • Classic chicken noodle
  • Vegetable
  • Minestrone with pasta
  • Cheesy enchilada
 
Starbucks Coffees
 

Fiddler, Fifer & Practical Café is the first location ever inside a Disney theme park where you can enjoy refreshing Starbucks coffee and espresso drinks — including flavored lattes, iced coffees and Frappuccino® blended beverages. The café also serves some of your favorite signature Starbucks breakfast sandwiches and pastries

Flo's V8 Cafe

Restaurant Info

 
Meals Served
 
Breakfast • Lunch • Dinner • Snacks

Premium 15%
Deluxe 10%
So-Cal 10%
So-Cal Select 10%
 
Location
 
Cars Land, California Adventure
 
Ambience
 

Cruise on in to Flo's V8 Cafe and fill up your tank on classic American cuisine with a new spin. Inspired by the timeless drive-up diners along Route 66, Flo's V8 Cafe celebrates the pioneering spirit of the open road. If you're looking for the most popular restaurant in all of Carburetor County, just head towards the signature 27-foot-tall neon V8 sign!
 
Menu
 

Get your engines revving in the morning with breakfast favorites like chicken tamales with scrambled eggs or French toast served with salted caramel and bananas. For lunch, try inventive cuisine like Veggie-Tater Bake or indulge in home-style rotisserie classics including pork loin, citrus turkey and New York strip loin. Top off your meal with delicious single-serve fruit pies including apple-cheddar and cherry flavors!
 
Dining Area and Patio
 

The food at Flo's is only half the fun! From both the huge glass windows of the interior dining area and the open-air patio, you can take in the majestic mountains and expanses of Ornament Valley — and even watch cars speed past on Radiator Springs Racers.

While you're eating and enjoying the view, be sure to look around to see the mementos from the singing career of the cafe owner, Flo from the Disney·Pixar movie Cars. Another section of the dining area is a museum that showcases the racing career of Cars legend Doc Hudson.
